   1.10 ARP 1/3 
  
     n   When a network device wants to transmit a packet     to another
 device it needs to know both the   IP     address   and the   physical address   of the
 destination.       
     n   IP address to physical address mapping is     maintained in
 the ARP   cache  . ï¿½         
     n   The ARP cache is constantly   updated  .        
     n   Network devices can identify   local   and   remote       addresses
 using the subnet mask.     
  
 

